[center][size=6][b]RHI — ReShade HDR Installer[/b][/size][/center]

One app to manage HDR mods across your entire PC game library. RHI auto-detects games from eight storefronts, installs and updates ReShade, RenoDX, frame limiters, DLSS/Streamline, OptiScaler, and more — all with per-game control and zero manual configuration.

[center][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/RankFTW/RHI/main/screenshots/game_view.png[/img][/center]

[color=#FF6600][b]⚠ Single-player only.[/b][/color] RHI installs ReShade with addon support, which may trigger anti-cheat in online games. Uninstall before playing multiplayer.

[line]

[size=5][b]Why RHI?[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]8-store detection[/b] — Steam, GOG, Epic, EA App, Ubisoft Connect, Xbox/Game Pass, Battle.net, Rockstar. No manual setup.
[*][b]8 managed components[/b] — ReShade, RenoDX, ReLimiter, Display Commander, OptiScaler, RE Framework, Luma Framework, DXVK. One-click install, update, and removal for each.
[*][b]46 shader packs[/b] — Essential, Recommended, and Extra categories. Global or per-game selection.
[*][b]DLSS & Streamline management[/b] — swap SR, Ray Reconstruction, and Frame Generation independently. Update or downgrade Streamline as a set. Per-game DLSS presets without NVIDIA Profile Inspector.
[*][b]Nvidia Profile Overrides[/b] — VSync, Low Latency, Smooth Motion, Power Mode, ReBAR, Multi Frame Generation, DLSS render scale (33–100%). All per-game, written directly to NVIDIA driver profiles.
[*][b]Batch deploy[/b] — update DLSS/Streamline versions and presets across multiple games at once.
[*][b]DLSS & Streamline Defaults[/b] — configure preferred versions, presets, and render scales. One-click Quick Apply per game.
[*][b]Profile Export/Import[/b] — back up all per-game NVIDIA profile settings to JSON. Restore after driver updates.
[*][b]Drag-and-drop[/b] — drop an exe, addon, preset, Luma archive, or URL. RHI figures out what to do.
[*][b]Three view modes[/b] — Detail View, Grid View, Simple View. Fresh installs default to Simple View.
[*][b]Game Launch[/b] — Steam uses -applaunch (with overlay and playtime tracking), Epic uses its protocol, everything else launches directly. Custom exe and arguments per game.
[*][b]Luma + RenoDX coexistence[/b] — for compatible games, both frameworks run side by side.
[*][b]Ryubing emulator support[/b] — 9 Switch game addons from Souperman9, downloaded and deployed in one click. Addons self-select which game is running.
[*][b]UE-Extended auto-configuration[/b] — reshade.ini [renodx] section and Engine.ini HDR settings are written automatically.
[*][b]Nexus Mods update alerts[/b] — GraphQL API, no API key required.
[*][b]Remote manifest[/b] — game-specific fixes pushed over the air without app updates.
[*][b]Foreign DLL protection[/b] — binary signature scanning prevents accidental overwrites of DXVK, Special K, ENB, etc.
[*][b]Addon file watcher[/b] — auto-detects new addons in your Downloads folder and prompts to install.
[*][b]Message of the Day[/b] — important notices delivered on launch when something changes.
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Managed Components[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b][url=https://reshade.me]ReShade[/url][/b] — Post-processing injection framework. Channels: Stable, Nightly, Custom (user DLLs), Legacy (pin to 6.0.0+), No Addons.
[*][b][url=https://github.com/clshortfuse/renodx]RenoDX[/url][/b] — HDR mod framework. Game-specific mods matched from the RenoDX wiki with generic Unreal/Unity/UE-Extended fallbacks.
[*][b][url=https://github.com/RankFTW/ReLimiter]ReLimiter[/url][/b] — Frame pacing addon with configurable OSD hotkey and shared presets.
[*][b][url=https://github.com/pmnoxx/display-commander]Display Commander[/url][/b] — Alternative frame rate limiter. Mutually exclusive with ReLimiter.
[*][b][url=https://github.com/optiscaler/OptiScaler]OptiScaler[/url][/b] — Upscaler redirection (DLSS ↔ FSR ↔ XeSS). Auto-downloads DLSS DLLs, handles ReShade coexistence, includes OptiPatcher for AMD/Intel.
[*][b][url=https://github.com/praydog/REFramework-nightly]RE Framework[/url][/b] — Required for ReShade on RE Engine games (Monster Hunter Wilds, Resident Evil, DMC5, SF6, etc.).
[*][b][url=https://github.com/Filoppi/Luma-Framework]Luma Framework[/url][/b] — DX11 HDR modding framework. Toggle per game — ReShade and RenoDX are swapped automatically.
[*][b][url=https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk]DXVK[/url][/b] — DirectX-to-Vulkan translation for DX8–DX10 games. Variants: Development, Stable, Lilium HDR (scRGB output). Per-game selection.
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Key Features[/b][/size]

[size=4][b]DLSS & Streamline[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Swap DLSS SR, Ray Reconstruction, and Frame Generation to any version independently
[*]Update or downgrade Streamline as a complete set
[*]DLSS presets per game — SR: Default/J/K/L/M · RR: Default/D/E · FG: Default/A/B
[*]DLSS render scale override: 33–100% per game for both SR and RR
[*]Multi Frame Generation (RTX 50 Series): Mode (Default/Fixed/Dynamic), Frame Count (2x–6x), Target FPS
[*]Quick Apply deploys your configured defaults to any game in one click
[*]Batch Deploy updates versions + presets across multiple games simultaneously
[*]Backup/restore per game (.original files)
[/list]

[size=4][b]Nvidia Profile Overrides[/b][/size]

All per-game via NVIDIA driver profiles. Requires admin (Task Scheduler-based persistent elevation available).

[list]
[*][b]VSync[/b] — Mode + Tear Control
[*][b]Low Latency[/b] — Off / On / Ultra
[*][b]Smooth Motion[/b] — Enable + APIs + Flip Pacing
[*][b]Power Mode[/b] — Adaptive / Prefer Max Performance / Optimal
[*][b]ReBAR[/b] — Enable / Mode / Size Limit
[*][b]Profile Export/Import[/b] — back up all settings to JSON, restore after driver updates
[/list]

[size=4][b]Global Nvidia Settings (Settings page)[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Shader Cache Size
[*]Shader Pre-Compile
[*]G-Sync Mode
[*]Preferred Refresh Rate
[*]Global ReBAR (On/Off + Size)
[*]DLSS On-Screen Indicator
[/list]

[size=4][b]Admin Mode[/b][/size]

Task Scheduler-based persistent elevation. Toggle Off/On in Settings. When enabled, RHI silently relaunches elevated on startup — no per-operation UAC prompts. Required for ReBAR, Low Latency (ULL), Smooth Motion, and CPU Scheduling writes.

[size=4][b]Per-Game Overrides[/b][/size]

DLL naming · Shader mode (Global/Custom/Select/Off) · Addon mode (Global/Select/Off) · Bitness · Graphics API · ReShade channel (Stable/Nightly/Custom/Legacy/No Addons) · DXVK variant · Launch exe + arguments · Update inclusion toggles · Wiki name mapping

[size=4][b]OptiScaler[/b][/size]

Upscaler redirection with automatic DLSS DLL downloads, ReShade coexistence, INI configuration, and OptiPatcher for AMD/Intel GPUs.

[size=4][b]HDR Gaming Database[/b][/size]

The RenoDX Info button links directly to HDR Gaming Database entries for supported games.

[size=4][b]UW Fix & Ultra+ Links[/b][/size]

Quick links to ultrawide fixes (Lyall, RoseTheFlower, p1xel8ted) and Ultra+ mods appear on game cards when available.

[line]

[size=5][b]Quick Start[/b][/size]

[list=1]
[*][b]Download and run RHI[/b] — your game library appears automatically.
[*][b]Pick a game[/b] from the sidebar. Search or use filter chips to narrow the list.
[*][b]Click Install[/b] on the components you want — ReShade, RenoDX, a frame limiter.
[*][b]Launch the game[/b], press [b]Home[/b] to open ReShade, go to [b]Add-ons[/b], and configure RenoDX.
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Download[/b][/size]

Grab the latest release from the [url=https://github.com/RankFTW/RHI/releases]GitHub Releases page[/url].

[b]Requirements:[/b]
[list]
[*]Windows 10/11 (x64)
[*][url=https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/8.0].NET 8 Desktop Runtime[/url]
[*]NVIDIA GPU recommended for DLSS/Streamline and Profile Override features (AMD/Intel supported for everything else)
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Troubleshooting[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Game not detected[/b] — Add Game in Settings — pick the game's exe and name it
[*][b]Xbox games missing[/b] — Click Refresh — Game Pass detection may need a moment
[*][b]ReShade not loading[/b] — Check the install path via 📁 — the DLL must sit next to the game exe
[*][b]Black screen (Unreal)[/b] — ReShade → Add-ons → RenoDX → set R10G10B10A2_UNORM to output size
[*][b]UE-Extended not working[/b] — Enable HDR in the game's display settings first
[*][b]Downloads failing[/b] — Click Refresh, or clear cache from Settings → Open Downloads Cache
[*][b]DLSS presets not applying[/b] — Enable Admin Mode in Settings, or run RHI as administrator
[*][b]Everything out of sync[/b] — Settings → Full Refresh clears all caches and re-scans
[/list]

For the full reference covering every feature, see the [url=https://github.com/RankFTW/RHI/blob/main/docs/DETAILED_GUIDE.md]Detailed Guide[/url].

